div1.p: United States of America, Western District of Washington } ss:

I hereby certify and return that I served the annexed Writ of Habeas Corpus on the therein named Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration of the United States by handing to and leaving a true and correct copy thereof with Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration of the United States at Seattle in the District on the 12th day of December, A.D. 1913
div1.ab: Joseph R. H. Jacoby, U.S. Marshal
div1.p: In the District Court of the United States For the Western District of Washington Northern Division
In the matter of the Petition of Albert H. Young and Kamsaburo Sugiura, alias B.K. Sugiura, aliens, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
Filed in the U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington, Northern Division Dec 13 1913 Frank L. Crosby By EML Deputy
R.W. McClellan, H.A.P. Myers & Walter L. Johnstone Attorney for Petitioners
